e":"HUMAN_APPROVAL","agentId":"OWNERAGENTTOKEN","action":"Review the FDAS request package and approve or reject initial intake.","description":"The business sponsor reviews the submitted request package for completeness, strategic alignment, and initial viability. An approval advances the request into the business and risk assessment stage.","inputArtifactId":"FDAS Request Package","outputArtifactId":"Stage 1 Approval Decision","handoffToAgentId":"OWNERAGENTTOKEN","handoffToPhase":"QA","handoffLabel":"Stage 1 approval hand-off to business and risk assessment","handoffProtocolId":"HANDOFF-CAPABILITYIDTOKEN-FDAS-STAGE1-APPROVAL","approverRoles":["Business Sponsor","Intake Coordinator"],"exitCriteria":["Request package reviewed","Strategic alignment confirmed","Initial screening decision recorded"],"templatePath":"/out/steps/fdas-stage1-approval-template.md","allowedToolIds":[],"executionNotes":"This step always pauses for explicit human approval. The workflow must not advance until the intake decision is captured.","artifactContract":{"requiredInputs":["FDAS Request Package","Business Case Summary","Scope Boundary Statement"],"expectedOutputs":["Stage 1 Approval Decision","Intake Review Notes","Conditions for Advancement"],"notes":"The stage 1 approval decision must document the rationale and any conditions placed on the request before it moves to assessment."}},{"id":"STEP-CAPABILITYIDTOKEN-3","name":"Business and Risk Assessment","phase":"QA","stepType":"HUMAN_TASK","agentId":"OWNERAGENTTOKEN","action":"Conduct the business impact, dependency, and risk assessment for the FDAS request.","description":"The business analyst and risk team perform a structured assessment of operational impact, upstream and downstream dependencies, feasibility, and risk posture. The output provides the evidence base needed for business validation.","inputArtifactId":"Stage 1 Approval Decision","outputArtifactId":"Business and Risk Assessment Report","handoffToAgentId":"OWNERAGENTTOKEN","handoffToPhase":"QA","handoffLabel":"Assessment report hand-off to business validation","handoffProtocolId":"HANDOFF-CAPABILITYIDTOKEN-FDAS-RISK-ASSESSMENT","exitCriteria":["Business impact documented","Dependencies and risks identified","Feasibility assessment completed","Assessment report submitted for validation"],"templatePath":"/out/steps/fdas-risk-assessment-template.md","allowedToolIds":[],"executionNotes":"This is a human-performed step. The assessment must be completed by the designated business analyst and risk officer before it advances to validation.","artifactContract":{"requiredInputs":["Stage 1 Approval Decision","FDAS Request Package","Intake Review Notes"],"expectedOutputs":["Business and Risk Assessment Report","Dependency Register","Risk and Control Summary"],"notes":"The assessment report must provide a clear and objective picture of business impact and risk before stakeholders can validate the request."}},{"id":"STEP-CAPABILITYIDTOKEN-4","name":"Stage 2 Approval - Business Validation","phase":"QA","stepType":"HUMAN_APPROVAL","agentId":"OWNERAGENTTOKEN","action":"Review the assessment report and validate or return the FDAS request for revision.","description":"Senior business stakeholders and the risk committee review the impact assessment, validate the business case against organisational priorities, and either approve advancement to the authorisation stage or return the request for revision.","inputArtifactId":"Business and Risk Assessment Report","outputArtifactId":"Stage 2 Approval Decision","handoffToAgentId":"OWNERAGENTTOKEN","handoffToPhase":"RELEASE","handoffLabel":"Stage 2 approval hand-off to compliance review","handoffProtocolId":"HANDOFF-CAPABILITYIDTOKEN-FDAS-STAGE2-APPROVAL","approverRoles":["Senior Business Stakeholder","Risk Committee Lead","Operations Manager"],"exitCriteria":["Assessment report reviewed","Business case validated against priorities","Risk posture accepted or conditions imposed","Stage 2 decision recorded"],"templatePath":"/out/steps/fdas-stage2-approval-template.md","allowedToolIds":[],"executionNotes":"This step always pauses for explicit human approval. The workflow must not advance until the business validation decision is captured.","artifactContract":{"requiredInputs":["Business and Risk Assessment Report","Dependency Register","Risk and Control Summary"],"expectedOutputs":["Stage 2 Approval Decision","Validation Review Notes","Outstanding Conditions Register"],"notes":"The stage 2 decision must record validation outcome, unresolved conditions, and any revised scope guidance before advancement."}},{"id":"STEP-CAPABILITYIDTOKEN-5","name":"Compliance and Regulatory Review","phase":"RELEASE","stepType":"HUMAN_TASK","agentId":"OWNERAGENTTOKEN","action":"Verify regulatory alignment, prepare sign-off documentation, and capture outstanding compliance conditions.","description":"The compliance officer reviews the validated FDAS request against applicable regulatory requirements, organisational policy, and audit obligations. The output is a compliance clearance package that supports executive sign-off.","inputArtifactId":"Stage 2 Approval Decision","outputArtifactId":"Compliance Clearance Package","handoffToAgentId":"OWNERAGENTTOKEN","handoffToPhase":"RELEASE","handoffLabel":"Compliance clearance hand-off to executive sign-off","handoffProtocolId":"HANDOFF-CAPABILITYIDTOKEN-FDAS-COMPLIANCE-REVIEW","exitCriteria":["Regulatory requirements reviewed","Policy alignment confirmed","Compliance conditions documented","Clearance package submitted for executive review"],"templatePath":"/out/steps/fdas-compliance-review-template.md","allowedToolIds":[],"executionNotes":"This is a human-performed step. The compliance officer must complete the review and submit the clearance package before the executive sign-off step can begin.","artifactContract":{"requiredInputs":["Stage 2 Approval Decision","Validation Review Notes","Outstanding Conditions Register"],"expectedOutputs":["Compliance Clearance Package","Regulatory Alignment Summary","Outstanding Compliance Conditions"],"notes":"The compliance clearance package must clearly state the regulatory and policy position so the executive committee can make an informed final decision."}},{"id":"STEP-CAPABILITYIDTOKEN-6","name":"Stage 3 Approval - Executive Sign-off","phase":"RELEASE","stepType":"HUMAN_APPROVAL","agentId":"OWNERAGENTTOKEN","action":"Provide final executive authorisation to proceed with the FDAS business use case.","description":"The executive sponsor reviews the compliance clearance package, validation decisions, and full request history. A formal sign-off authorises the business use case to move into execution. Any conditions or restrictions imposed at this stage are binding.","inputArtifactId":"Compliance Clearance Package","outputArtifactId":"Executive Authorisation Record","handoffLabel":"Executive authorisation hand-off to workflow closure","handoffProtocolId":"HANDOFF-CAPABILITYIDTOKEN-FDAS-STAGE3-APPROVAL","approverRoles":["Executive Sponsor","Chief Business Officer","Accountable Officer"],"exitCriteria":["Compliance clearance reviewed","Executive decision recorded","Authorisation conditions documented","Business use case cleared for execution"],"templatePath":"/out/steps/fdas-stage3-approval-template.md","allowedToolIds":[],"executionNotes":"This step always pauses for explicit human approval. The workflow must not advance until the executive authorisation is captured and recorded.","artifactContract":{"requiredInputs":["Compliance Clearance Package","Stage 2 Approval Decision","Regulatory Alignment Summary"],"expectedOutputs":["Executive Authorisation Record","Approved Scope Statement","Execution Conditions Register"],"notes":"The executive authorisation record is the binding approval document. It must capture the decision, conditions, and authorised scope before execution begins."}}]}'::TEXT,
        'OWNERAGENTTOKEN',
        seed.owner_agent_id
      ),
      'CAPABILITYIDTOKEN',
      seed.capability_slug
